✅ Use a pre-designed resume template ->> new template 
✅ Make the resume fit on 1 page ->> use https://www.resumemaker.online/
✅ Include words from job description ->> emphasis on it
✅ Include company name you are applying to ->> need more info on this 
✅ Does your first item on your resume reflect what they are looking for? ->> need to be keen on it 
✅ Experience titles demonstrate value ->> if experience in years show it else leave it 
✅ Do you have an online link? -> for github / blog post 
✅ Remove the word “I” ->> understood 
✅ No buzzwords describing how great you are ->> flattering wont make you great  
✅  * Are you using Action words? ->> what you did / what did you do ??
✅  * Measure everything in terms of impact, don’t just describe your responsibilities ->> very important 
✅  * Technical Knowledge/Skills should include what they are looking for. Only show years if it is impressive
✅  * Include only sections/items that are impressive: Experience, Projects, Education, Technical Skills  
✅ No typos or bad grammar ->> understood 
